01:10:42,240 --> 01:10:43,195
Hi.

953
01:10:43,280 --> 01:10:44,554
What's this?

954
01:10:44,640 --> 01:10:47,393
It's just a little something
I thought I'd bring by...

955
01:10:47,480 --> 01:10:49,152
- Flowers?
- Yeah.

956
01:10:49,240 --> 01:10:53,028
You think flowers
are going to make me forgive you?

957
01:10:53,120 --> 01:10:56,874
No. No, I do not think that.
I don't think that at all.

958
01:10:56,960 --> 01:11:00,157
Then what the hell are you doing here?

959
01:11:00,240 --> 01:11:06,839
OK, look. To be honest, I realize that
I've made the biggest mistake of my life.

960
01:11:06,920 --> 01:11:13,109
I'm desperately in love with you and I'd
do anything for us to be together again.

961
01:11:18,520 --> 01:11:20,511
I would.

962
01:11:28,960 --> 01:11:30,871
Oh, God.

963
01:11:30,960 --> 01:11:32,951
They're beautiful.

964
01:11:33,960 --> 01:11:35,552
- I'm sorry.
- It's OK.

965
01:11:35,640 --> 01:11:38,598
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

966
01:11:38,680 --> 01:11:44,277
What do you think about today after work
you come by my place around seven

967
01:11:44,360 --> 01:11:50,230
- and I'll make us a nice dinner?
- Seven? I'd love to.

968
01:12:16,640 --> 01:12:18,631
Matt?

969
01:12:19,600 --> 01:12:21,591
Matt?

970
01:12:24,880 --> 01:12:27,269
- Oh, my God!
- Hey, Jenny.

971
01:12:28,520 --> 01:12:30,636
Matt, it's beautiful.

972
01:12:30,720 --> 01:12:33,678
Oh, what is that? Is that for me?

973
01:12:33,760 --> 01:12:37,230
It is. It's a little something I got you cos...

974
01:12:37,320 --> 01:12:40,676
I wanna apologize
for the terrible way that I've treated you.

975
01:12:40,760 --> 01:12:44,116
- It just wasn't right.
- You're so sweet. You didn't have to.

976
01:12:44,200 --> 01:12:46,475
- It's true, I'm sorry.
- What is it?

977
01:12:46,560 --> 01:12:50,951
No peeking, OK? I want it
to be a surprise. Let's have a toast.

978
01:12:51,040 --> 01:12:53,600
(Jenny) You are amazing.

979
01:12:53,680 --> 01:12:56,558
(Matt) To second chances.

980
01:12:57,560 --> 01:12:59,835
(Jenny) To second chances.

981
01:13:01,400 --> 01:13:05,791
The man's not bad.
He might have a future in our business.

982
01:13:06,320 --> 01:13:08,515
You know, deep down,

983
01:13:08,600 --> 01:13:13,116
I had a feeling that you'd realize
your mistake and come back to me.

984
01:13:13,200 --> 01:13:15,191
You are wise.

985
01:13:17,040 --> 01:13:19,918
- Do you wanna know a secret?
- Sure.

986
01:13:23,480 --> 01:13:25,994
That's why I didn't kill you.

987
01:13:26,080 --> 01:13:28,071
(forced laugh)

988
01:13:49,640 --> 01:13:50,868
Matt?

989
01:13:50,960 --> 01:13:53,599
You are the sweetest guy I've ever met.

990
01:13:53,680 --> 01:13:56,592
- Oh, no, no, I'm not.
- Yes, yes, you are.

991
01:13:57,520 --> 01:14:00,034
You're sweet.

992
01:14:00,120 --> 01:14:02,111
Yummy.

993
01:14:03,360 --> 01:14:05,555
Matt?!

994
01:14:05,640 --> 01:14:07,437
What are you doing here?

995
01:14:07,520 --> 01:14:09,988
Me?! What are you doing here?

996
01:14:10,080 --> 01:14:13,311
You said your life was in danger.
And what's she doing here?

997
01:14:13,400 --> 01:14:16,312
- Who's that? Do we know her?
- I don't know her.

998
01:14:16,400 --> 01:14:17,549
I don't know her.

999
01:14:17,640 --> 01:14:22,668
You know how you tried to steal my
boyfriend by being such a big, fat whore?

1000
01:14:22,760 --> 01:14:25,274
- It didn't work.
- Jenny, stop. Let me handle this.

1001
01:14:25,360 --> 01:14:26,759
- Are you back with her?
- No.

1002
01:14:26,840 --> 01:14:28,831
- What?
- Yeah.

1003
01:14:28,920 --> 01:14:31,878
Look, it's very complicated, OK?

1004
01:14:31,960 --> 01:14:34,679
How could you do this?
You told me you loved me.

1005
01:14:34,760 --> 01:14:37,593
Hannah, please, just do me a favor, OK?
Just leave.

1006
01:14:37,680 --> 01:14:41,719
I mean, just try to have a little self-respect.
You're starting to look pathetic.

1007
01:14:41,800 --> 01:14:47,318
Matt! You are not... Oh, my God. There you
are. Thank God. I've been calling you all day.

1008
01:14:47,400 --> 01:14:49,994
Playoff tickets. Amazing seats. You and me.

1009
01:14:50,080 --> 01:14:52,674
- Not now.
- Tonight. Third base line. Yahoo!

1010
01:14:52,760 --> 01:14:56,070
- Now is a terrible time, OK?
- Hey, what's in the box?

1011
01:14:56,160 --> 01:15:00,631
- Stay away from that box.
- You know, Hannah,

1012
01:15:00,720 --> 01:15:04,599
why don't you just run along before I have
to kick your ass back to Munchkin Land?

1013
01:15:04,680 --> 01:15:07,592
- Stay away from it.
- It looks big, it might be a nice present.

1014
01:15:07,680 --> 01:15:11,468
- Are you threatening me?
- Push me one more time and you'll find out.

1015
01:15:11,560 --> 01:15:15,678
Oh, yeah? What are you going to do?
Squash me with your gigantic feet?

1016
01:15:15,760 --> 01:15:18,479
- That's it!
- Don't touch me!

1017
01:15:20,000 --> 01:15:24,118
Just do me a favor and leave
and take Hannah with you...

1018
01:15:24,800 --> 01:15:28,110
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, my God! You're G-Girl.

1019
01:15:28,680 --> 01:15:30,955
You have been doing G-Girl?

1020
01:15:31,840 --> 01:15:35,753
- Vaughn, open the box!
- Go! Go! Go! Watch the van!

1021
01:15:37,440 --> 01:15:39,510
Open the damn box!

1022
01:15:41,720 --> 01:15:43,039
Aargh!

1023
01:15:43,120 --> 01:15:46,430
- It's not much of a present.
- Agh!

1024
01:15:46,520 --> 01:15:48,511
I'm sorry.

1025
01:15:51,120 --> 01:15:53,111
You bastard!

1026
01:16:01,760 --> 01:16:04,479
Matt, that's a weird rock.

1027
01:16:04,560 --> 01:16:05,879
Ah.

1028
01:16:05,960 --> 01:16:09,919
A happy ending for everybody.
Well done, Mr. Saunders.

1029
01:16:10,000 --> 01:16:12,753
You did this? You helped him?

1030
01:16:12,840 --> 01:16:17,152
I'm really sorry.
You did throw a shark at me, you know.

1031
01:16:17,240 --> 01:16:20,915
Besides, Bedlam's gonna retire. It'll be OK.

1032
01:16:21,880 --> 01:16:23,472
You idiot!

1033
01:16:25,440 --> 01:16:28,637
Looks like you're done, honey.

1034
01:16:28,720 --> 01:16:33,316
You always thought
you were so much better than me.

1035
01:16:33,400 --> 01:16:35,197
Now it's my turn.

1036
01:16:35,280 --> 01:16:38,431
Now I'll be the one with the powers.

1037
01:16:38,520 --> 01:16:41,592
You'll be just plain old Jenny Johnson.

1038
01:16:42,520 --> 01:16:45,193
We're having a moment here.

1039
01:16:46,800 --> 01:16:51,954
- Not so tough now, huh?!
- Hannah, don't let her touch the rock!

1040
01:17:04,880 --> 01:17:07,110
Hannah!

1041
01:17:09,840 --> 01:17:11,239
Oh, no! Hannah!

1042
01:17:12,960 --> 01:17:15,428
I can't even see her. We gotta get down there.

1043
01:17:15,520 --> 01:17:17,511
Oh, man!

1044
01:17:18,440 --> 01:17:20,396
I think she's dead, Matt.

1045
01:17:20,480 --> 01:17:23,153
- I'm sorry. Let her go.
- We gotta dig her out!

1046
01:17:23,240 --> 01:17:26,471
- We gotta start the grieving process.
- Are you crazy?

1047
01:17:26,560 --> 01:17:29,028
- Come here. Give me a hug, bear cub.
- You!

1048
01:17:30,960 --> 01:17:33,554
I thought you were just a jerk!

1049
01:17:33,640 --> 01:17:35,915
Now I find out you're really stupid.

1050
01:17:36,000 --> 01:17:38,150
Teaming up with Barry?!

1051
01:17:44,520 --> 01:17:49,196
You broke my heart
and now I'm gonna break your everything.

1052
01:17:52,840 --> 01:17:54,751
Hey!

1053
01:17:54,840 --> 01:17:57,559
Let go of my boyfriend, you crazy bitch!

1054
01:17:58,480 --> 01:18:00,994
Bring it!

1055
01:18:05,960 --> 01:18:08,076
Oh, man!

1056
01:18:08,160 --> 01:18:10,515
Yes, girl fight!

1057
01:18:11,240 --> 01:18:13,037
Stupid!

1058
01:18:14,080 --> 01:18:16,036
Matt!

1059
01:18:23,160 --> 01:18:25,151
No!

1060
01:18:25,760 --> 01:18:27,512
Hannah!

1061
01:18:27,600 --> 01:18:29,158
Hannah, are you OK?

1062
01:18:30,080 --> 01:18:31,638
Oh, no!

1063
01:18:38,480 --> 01:18:40,550
You rat!

1064
01:18:43,680 --> 01:18:48,071
Oh, Matt. Matt, Matt, are you OK?

1065
01:18:51,400 --> 01:18:53,311
Uh-oh.

1066
01:19:12,000 --> 01:19:13,991
Wow!

1067
01:19:17,160 --> 01:19:19,435
Hannah, stop. Come on, stop.

1068
01:19:19,520 --> 01:19:20,953
- Are you OK?
- I'm fine.

1069
01:19:21,040 --> 01:19:24,112
I'm fine too. I thought I twinged my knee,
but I'm all right.

1070
01:19:24,200 --> 01:19:27,795
Come on. Forget about them. Let's go.

1071
01:19:27,880 --> 01:19:30,030
Come on.

1072
01:19:32,160 --> 01:19:35,550
They're gonna kill each other. This way.

1073
01:19:37,560 --> 01:19:40,632
- Hey, it's you.
- Are you with them?

1074
01:19:40,720 --> 01:19:42,711
As a matter of fact, I am.

1075
01:19:43,760 --> 01:19:46,035
They went down there.

1076
01:20:03,600 --> 01:20:06,068
Stop!

1077
01:20:06,560 --> 01:20:10,439
Look at yourself.
You're terrifying these people.

1078
01:20:13,640 --> 01:20:18,031
Jenny... Jenny,
this has gotta stop right now, OK?

1079
01:20:18,120 --> 01:20:19,553
Please.

1080
01:20:19,640 --> 01:20:21,995
Just give me that, OK?

1081
01:20:22,080 --> 01:20:24,514
There you go. Just give it to me.

1082
01:20:24,600 --> 01:20:28,229
Wow. That was a lot heavier than I thought.

1083
01:20:29,320 --> 01:20:31,356
Hi.

1084
01:20:31,440 --> 01:20:36,070
Look, God knows
I don't want you mad at me, OK?

1085
01:20:36,160 --> 01:20:38,594
And I'm sorry if I ever hurt you.

1086
01:20:38,680 --> 01:20:42,593
And yeah, I know what we had
was something special.

1087
01:20:42,680 --> 01:20:44,910
And at times it was great.

1088
01:20:45,000 --> 01:20:49,869
But it wasn't love, all right?
And deep down, you know that.

1089
01:20:51,040 --> 01:20:56,239
You're a great girl.
And you deserve to be with the perfect guy.

1090
01:20:56,320 --> 01:20:57,992
- You do.
- I do.

1091
01:20:58,080 --> 01:21:03,279
And I know who the perfect guy for you is.
And he's here, right here, right now.

1092
01:21:03,360 --> 01:21:05,351
Professor.

1093
01:21:07,840 --> 01:21:10,070
- What?
- Barry?

1094
01:21:10,920 --> 01:21:13,434
- Go on, Professor, tell her.
- Tell her what?

1095
01:21:13,520 --> 01:21:16,273
She's my mortal enemy?
I want nothing but her destruction?

1096
01:21:16,360 --> 01:21:21,309
- Come on, Barry, please.
- Please stop calling me Barry.

1097
01:21:21,400 --> 01:21:25,029
It's true. This guy,
he's got a shrine to you in his house.

1098
01:21:25,120 --> 01:21:28,715
There are pictures of you
all over the walls, just of you.

1099
01:21:28,800 --> 01:21:32,156
This guy, he is hooked on you.
He really is.

1100
01:21:33,080 --> 01:21:35,594
Is that true?

1101
01:21:41,360 --> 01:21:46,514
Come on. You gotta open your heart to her.
It's now or never.

1102
01:21:46,600 --> 01:21:49,353
It may be a little true.

1103
01:21:51,360 --> 01:21:56,115
OK, OK, that's a good start.
Come on, Barry. Barry, come on.

1104
01:21:56,200 --> 01:21:58,714
All right, all right!

1105
01:21:58,800 --> 01:22:00,791
It's completely true.

1106
01:22:02,280 --> 01:22:04,794
I love you.

1107
01:22:04,880 --> 01:22:07,678
I've always loved you.

1108
01:22:07,760 --> 01:22:12,151
But if you love me so much, then how come
you're always trying to hurt me?

1109
01:22:12,240 --> 01:22:17,360
Because you hurt me. Because you
broke my heart into a billion pieces.

1110
01:22:17,440 --> 01:22:20,193
You ignored me.

1111
01:22:20,280 --> 01:22:22,271
You left me behind.

1112
01:22:24,200 --> 01:22:29,797
So I thought if I had the powers,
you may learn to love me

1113
01:22:29,880 --> 01:22:33,111
the way I have always loved you.

1114
01:22:37,240 --> 01:22:39,231
Are you sure?

1115
01:22:40,560 --> 01:22:42,676
Do you really love me?

1116
01:22:46,640 --> 01:22:48,790
Oh, yeah.

1117
01:23:00,280 --> 01:23:03,192
It's over. Can you believe it?
I'm free. You were great.

1118
01:23:03,280 --> 01:23:04,759
I can't believe that fight.

1119
01:23:04,840 --> 01:23:07,798
I still think she'd kick my butt,
but I got a few good punches in.

1120
01:23:07,880 --> 01:23:10,838
You saved my ass in there.
You were wonderful.

1121
01:23:10,920 --> 01:23:13,957
And I'm really sorry
I didn't explain things to you sooner,

1122
01:23:14,040 --> 01:23:18,431
- but I was just trying to protect you.
- I totally understand.

1123
01:23:18,520 --> 01:23:19,589
Good.

1124
01:23:19,680 --> 01:23:23,559
- Oh, my God, my hair.
- Oh, it doesn't look that bad. You can fix it.

1125
01:23:23,640 --> 01:23:25,517
Here, try this on.

1126
01:23:25,600 --> 01:23:27,397
Thanks.

1127
01:23:28,720 --> 01:23:31,154
See? Adorable.

1128
01:23:31,240 --> 01:23:33,435
- Yes, you are.
- No, not me.

1129
01:23:33,520 --> 01:23:36,193
- Come here.
- Agh!

1130
01:23:36,280 --> 01:23:37,952
- Tight.
- Oh, I'm so sorry.

1131
01:23:38,040 --> 01:23:41,589
- It's OK.
- I'm still getting used to all of this.

1132
01:23:41,680 --> 01:23:47,437
You and me both. And you know, we're going
to have to talk about the relationship too.

1133
01:23:47,520 --> 01:23:51,229
- Talk? You mean...
- Your powers.

1134
01:23:51,320 --> 01:23:55,996
Just cos you have 'em doesn't mean
you have to use 'em, you know what I mean?

1135
01:23:56,080 --> 01:23:59,072
You're a little scared of me.

1136
01:23:59,160 --> 01:24:01,958
What? Scared?
No, come on, I'm not scared at all.

1137
01:24:02,040 --> 01:24:04,031
Come here.

1138
01:24:12,760 --> 01:24:14,557
Are you ready?

1139
01:24:14,640 --> 01:24:18,758
Yeah! I am. I'm ready.

1140
01:24:18,840 --> 01:24:21,354
OK. Here we go.

1141
01:24:25,720 --> 01:24:27,915
OK, all right, I got it.

1142
01:24:34,560 --> 01:24:38,997
- Hold on, I think I tweaked something.
- Oh, you poor baby.

1143
01:24:48,800 --> 01:24:50,836
What the hell were you doing?!

1144
01:24:52,920 --> 01:24:55,036
Sorry. Sorry.

1145
01:25:06,840 --> 01:25:08,990
Oh.

1146
01:25:09,080 --> 01:25:12,595
I brought it down for you.
Peace offering.

1147
01:25:17,280 --> 01:25:20,238
You've done so much for us.
We couldn't be happier.

1148
01:25:20,320 --> 01:25:22,788
- How...? How...?
- Asteroids.

1149
01:25:22,880 --> 01:25:26,111
Most of that will just buff right out.

1150
01:25:30,600 --> 01:25:33,194
- I'll fix that.
- I could trick it out for you.

1151
01:25:33,280 --> 01:25:36,636
Rocket launchers, laser cannons,
voice-activated battle armor.

1152
01:25:36,720 --> 01:25:38,870
- (police radio)
- Do you hear something?

1153
01:25:38,960 --> 01:25:41,315
- No.
- There's a 747 in trouble.

1154
01:25:41,400 --> 01:25:43,994
It's a 727. Time to go to work.

1155
01:25:44,960 --> 01:25:47,349
You need a hand?

1156
01:25:48,280 --> 01:25:50,669
- A hand?
- Yeah, any help?

1157
01:25:51,680 --> 01:25:54,353
I never had any help.

1158
01:25:54,440 --> 01:25:56,908
- Could be some heavy lifting.
- Yeah?

1159
01:25:57,000 --> 01:25:58,797
- OK.
- Yeah? Really?

1160
01:25:58,880 --> 01:26:02,509
- Yes.
- Yes! All right! Whoo!

1161
01:26:04,560 --> 01:26:06,915
OK, ready. Whoo! Here I go.

1162
01:26:14,720 --> 01:26:16,597
Yeah!

1163
01:26:17,480 --> 01:26:20,358
- Love you, honey!
- We'll be waiting!

1164
01:26:22,120 --> 01:26:26,159
What are we gonna do with this stuff?
Wanna get a beer?

1165
01:26:26,240 --> 01:26:28,310
- Sure.
- Let's do it.

1166
01:26:28,640 --> 01:26:32,030
# And the earth will be our home

1167
01:26:32,120 --> 01:26:35,510
# And the sky our starry dome

1168
